  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Priyansh, it's been a while! Honestly, the rain today feels perfect for a chat. How was your day?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey Maya, yeah it’s been some time. Tired today, couldn’t sleep well. Rain does feel nice, but I’m too sleepy to enjoy much. How about you?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds rough. Sleep loss is tough — what’s on your mind today?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Work stress, mostly. You know how it is — deadlines, updates, everything feels like it’s due yesterday. And I’ve been stuck in a loop of not being able to focus. Kya sooroon (feeling). How do you handle stress?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get that — work stress can eat into your day. I take small pauses with a cup of tea and a deep breath. What helps you reset?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Tea helps, yeah. Sometimes I just step out for five minutes, even if it’s raining. Helps clear my head a bit. But most times I just end up scrolling mindlessly. Not really helping. You know how it is."
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Taking a walk in the rain sounds peaceful — better than scrolling, for sure. Next time, try listening to a song you love while walking. What’s on your playlist?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Mostly Bollywood songs. Old ones, like Arijit Singh or Kumar Sanu. The kind that makes you feel everything. But honestly, right now I just listen to anything that drowns out my thoughts. You know? It’s been a rough few days."
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Bollywood old songs are magic — they really make you feel. Listening to drown out thoughts makes sense. What song lifts you the most right now?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Channa Mereya\" from Raazi, maybe. It’s haunting, you know? Sometimes I just listen to it on loop. But honestly, nothing really lifts me these days. I’m just… stuck."
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "\"Channa Mereya\" is a beautiful song — it's okay to let it play on loop when you're feeling stuck. What part of the song moves you the most?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The part where she sings about memories and longing… it just hits. Like, I don’t even know why. Maybe because it feels like it’s singing for all the things I can’t put into words. But I should probably stop listening to sad songs at 2 am. Not helping."
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I get that — songs often speak for what we can’t say. Still, a little sadness in music is okay. What’s next on your mind now?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Honestly? Not sure. I think I just need to sleep. Or maybe take a real break from work for once. But with deadlines… you know how it is. I’ll think about it. Thanks for the chat, Maya."
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "You're welcome — take the break you need, even if just for a little. Tell me how you feel after?"
    }
  ],
